  <description>Plants to 5 mm. Stems to 3.5 mm. Leaves to 2.5 × 1 mm, lanceolate or
        ovate-lanceolate to obovate, acuminate, not or weakly concave, margin of lanceolate leaves
        somewhat reflexed when dry, serrulate in distal 1/3, rarely below leaf median; costa ending
        near apex; proximal cells 65–135 × 15–45 µm, distal cells 36–66 × 12–27 µm; marginal cells
        sometimes longer that medial laminal cells, reaching 150 µm. Calyptra entire at base. Spores
        21–33 µm.</description>
  <phenology>Capsules mature Aug–Jan.</phenology>
  <habitat>Early pioneer on wet mineral soil, river banks, fields;</habitat>
  <elevation>low to moderate elevations;</elevation>
