  <discussion>Physcomitrella patens is fairly variable in leaf shape and stature. The species is
        similar to Aphanorrhegma, with which it is broadly sympatric, but far less common. It
        differs from A. serratum by the thin-walled exothecial cells and the unlobed
        calyptra.</discussion>
